com.github.katjahahn.parser.coffheader

Enum FileCharacteristic

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<FileCharacteristic>
      • com.github.katjahahn.parser.coffheader.FileCharacteristic
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Characteristic, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<FileCharacteristic>

    public enum FileCharacteristic
extends java.lang.Enum<FileCharacteristic>
implements Characteristic
    Represents the flags that indicate the attributes of the file.

    Descriptions taken from the PECOFF specification.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • IMAGE_FILE_RELOCS_STRIPPED

        public static final FileCharacteristic IMAGE_FILE_RELOCS_STRIPPED
        Windows CE, and Windows NT® and later. This indicates that the file does not contain base relocations and must therefore be loaded at its preferred base address. If the base address is not available, the loader reports an error. The default behavior of the linker is to strip base relocations from executable (EXE) files.

      • IMAGE_FILE_EXECUTABLE_IMAGE

        public static final FileCharacteristic IMAGE_FILE_EXECUTABLE_IMAGE
        This indicates that the image file is valid and can be run. If this flag is not set, it indicates a linker error.

      • IMAGE_FILE_LINE_NUMS_STRIPPED

        public static final FileCharacteristic IMAGE_FILE_LINE_NUMS_STRIPPED
        COFF line numbers have been removed. This flag is deprecated and should be zero.

      • IMAGE_FILE_LOCAL_SYMS_STRIPPED

        public static final FileCharacteristic IMAGE_FILE_LOCAL_SYMS_STRIPPED
        COFF symbol table entries for local symbols have been removed. This flag is deprecated and should be zero.

      • IMAGE_FILE_AGGRESSIVE_WS_TRIM

        public static final FileCharacteristic IMAGE_FILE_AGGRESSIVE_WS_TRIM
        Obsolete. Aggressively trim working set. This flag is deprecated for Windows 2000 and later and must be zero.

      • IMAGE_FILE_LARGE_ADDRESS_AWARE
